    "body": "Hi @marcosmartinez7, we only (officially) support node's LTS versions, as you can read [here](https://hardhat.org/hardhat-runner/docs/reference/stability-guarantees#node.js-versions-support).\r\n\r\nThat being said, maybe having that in the engines section is too restrictive, since things are likely to work in non-LTS versions too (maybe).\r\n\r\n@alcuadrado should we drop the `engines` from the `package.json`, and replace it with some warning similar to the solidity one?",
